## Key Bug Fixes This Session

### Deployment
- Railway blocked by next@14.2.29 CVEs → upgraded to 15.5.12
- `next` was missing from root package.json → Vercel couldn't detect framework
- `outputFileTracingRoot` was inside `experimental` → moved to top-level (Next.js 15)
- `force-dynamic` added to root layout → prevents Clerk prerender crash
- turbo-ignore was skipping builds due to same commit hash

### Map Crashes (client-side exceptions)
- MapEdge `sourceId`/`targetId` returned from API but D3 needs `source`/`target` → fixed in personalized route
- D3 reads `parentElement.clientHeight` which is 0 inside `max-w-2xl` layout → fixed to use `window.innerWidth/Height`
- framer-motion v11: `exit` on `motion.div` without `AnimatePresence` throws on unmount → wrapped in AnimatePresence
- `redis.setex(key, ttl, value)` has wrong arg order for @upstash/redis → use `redis.set(key, value, {ex: ttl})`

### Security (previous session)
- Rate limiting on 6 endpoints, security headers, CORS locked to APP_URL
- Embedding validated before pgvector raw SQL
- AuthError class + apiError() — all 33 routes return proper 401/403/500

### Data/Logic
- EMBED_PROFILE QStash job unhandled → implemented
- weekKey UTC bug → getISOWeekKey() in lib/utils.ts
- signalProfile.create → upsert for idempotency
- completedCount counted started sessions → fixed to count completedAt NOT NULL

